adjectives.description: uncalm (comparative more uncalm, superlative most uncalm)

examples: The ship rocked on the uncalm sea.

verbs.description: uncalm (third-person singular simple present uncalms, present participle uncalming, simple past and past participle uncalmed)

entries.meaning: (transitive, obsolete) To disturb from a state of calm.
examples: What strange disquiet has uncalm'd your breast
